main event: A pilot spotted a bright, white, lighted streak object while flying at an altitude of 15 degrees elevation, 20 degrees right of the nose of the aircraft, on January 16, 1963.
interesting points: The object appeared to be falling vertically and burned out after approximately 1.5 seconds of observation.
The object had a trail of flame and sparks that was seven times the length of the object itself.
The object was brighter than a typical meteorite.
The radar contact on the object was poor due to bad visibility at the time of the sighting.
The pilot suggested the object could have been a reentry of a satellite.
sighted object: a bright, white, lighted streak object
